31 TNode<IntPtrT> PointerToSeqStringData(TNode<String> seq_string) {
32 CSA_DCHECK(this,
33 IsSequentialStringInstanceType(LoadInstanceType(seq_string)));
34 static_assert(OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(SeqOneByteString) ==
35 OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(SeqTwoByteString));
36 return IntPtrAdd(BitcastTaggedToWord(seq_string),
37 IntPtrConstant(OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(SeqOneByteString) -
38 kHeapObjectTag));
39 }
40
41 TNode<Uint8T> GetChar(TNode<SeqOneByteString> seq_string, int index) {
42 size_t effective_offset = OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(SeqOneByteString) +
43 sizeof(SeqOneByteString::Char) * index -
44 kHeapObjectTag;
45 return Load<Uint8T>(seq_string, IntPtrConstant(effective_offset));
46 }
47
48 // Jumps to {target} if the first two characters of {seq_string} equal
49 // {pattern} ignoring case.
50 void JumpIfStartsWithIgnoreCase(TNode<SeqOneByteString> seq_string,
51 const char* pattern, Label* target) {
52 size_t effective_offset =
53 OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(SeqOneByteString) - kHeapObjectTag;
54 TNode<Uint16T> raw =
55 Load<Uint16T>(seq_string, IntPtrConstant(effective_offset));
56 DCHECK_EQ(strlen(pattern), 2);
57#if V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
58 int raw_pattern = (pattern[0] << 8) + pattern[1];
59#else
60 int raw_pattern = pattern[0] + (pattern[1] << 8);
61#endif
62 GotoIf(Word32Equal(Word32Or(raw, Int32Constant(0x2020)),
63 Int32Constant(raw_pattern)),
64 target);
65 }
66
67 TNode<BoolT> IsNonAlpha(TNode<Uint8T> character) {
68 return Uint32GreaterThan(
69 Int32Sub(Word32Or(character, Int32Constant(0x20)), Int32Constant('a')),
70 Int32Constant('z' - 'a'));
71 }
72
73 enum class ToLowerCaseKind {
74 kToLowerCase,
75 kToLocaleLowerCase,
76 };
77 void ToLowerCaseImpl(TNode<String> string, TNode<Object> maybe_locales,
78 TNode<Context> context, ToLowerCaseKind kind,
79 std::function<void(TNode<Object>)> ReturnFct);
80};

82TF_BUILTIN(StringToLowerCaseIntl, IntlBuiltinsAssembler) {
83 const auto string = Parameter<String>(Descriptor::kString);
84 ToLowerCaseImpl(string, TNode<Object>() /*maybe_locales*/, TNode<Context>(),
85 ToLowerCaseKind::kToLowerCase,
86 [this](TNode<Object> ret) { Return(ret); });
87}

91 auto context = Parameter<Context>(Descriptor::kContext);

93 TNode<String> string =

96 Return(CallBuiltin(Builtin::kStringToLowerCaseIntl, context, string));

99TF_BUILTIN(StringPrototypeToLocaleLowerCase, IntlBuiltinsAssembler) {
100 TNode<Int32T> argc =
101 UncheckedParameter<Int32T>(Descriptor::kJSActualArgumentsCount);
102 CodeStubArguments args(this, argc);
103 TNode<Object> maybe_string = args.GetReceiver();
104 TNode<Context> context = Parameter<Context>(Descriptor::kContext);
105 TNode<Object> maybe_locales = args.GetOptionalArgumentValue(0);
106 TNode<String> string =
107 ToThisString(context, maybe_string, "String.prototype.toLocaleLowerCase");
108 ToLowerCaseImpl(string, maybe_locales, context,
109 ToLowerCaseKind::kToLocaleLowerCase,
110 [&args](TNode<Object> ret) { args.PopAndReturn(ret); });
111}
112
113void IntlBuiltinsAssembler::ToLowerCaseImpl(
114 TNode<String> string, TNode<Object> maybe_locales, TNode<Context> context,
115 ToLowerCaseKind kind, std::function<void(TNode<Object>)> ReturnFct) {
116 Label call_c(this), return_string(this), runtime(this, Label::kDeferred);
117
118 // Unpack strings if possible, and bail to runtime unless we get a one-byte
119 // flat string.
120 ToDirectStringAssembler to_direct(
121 state(), string, ToDirectStringAssembler::kDontUnpackSlicedStrings);
122 to_direct.TryToDirect(&runtime);
123
124 if (kind == ToLowerCaseKind::kToLocaleLowerCase) {
125 Label fast(this), check_locale(this);
126 // Check for fast locales.
127 GotoIf(IsUndefined(maybe_locales), &fast);
128 // Passing a Smi as locales requires performing a ToObject conversion
129 // followed by reading the length property and the "indexed" properties of
130 // it until a valid locale is found.
131 GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(maybe_locales), &runtime);
132 GotoIfNot(IsString(CAST(maybe_locales)), &runtime);
133 GotoIfNot(IsSeqOneByteString(CAST(maybe_locales)), &runtime);
134 TNode<SeqOneByteString> locale = CAST(maybe_locales);
135 TNode<Uint32T> locale_length = LoadStringLengthAsWord32(locale);
136 GotoIf(Int32LessThan(locale_length, Int32Constant(2)), &runtime);
137 GotoIf(IsNonAlpha(GetChar(locale, 0)), &runtime);
138 GotoIf(IsNonAlpha(GetChar(locale, 1)), &runtime);
139 GotoIf(Word32Equal(locale_length, Int32Constant(2)), &check_locale);
140 GotoIf(Word32NotEqual(locale_length, Int32Constant(5)), &runtime);
141 GotoIf(Word32NotEqual(GetChar(locale, 2), Int32Constant('-')), &runtime);
142 GotoIf(IsNonAlpha(GetChar(locale, 3)), &runtime);
143 GotoIf(IsNonAlpha(GetChar(locale, 4)), &runtime);
144 Goto(&check_locale);
145
146 Bind(&check_locale);
147 JumpIfStartsWithIgnoreCase(locale, "az", &runtime);
148 JumpIfStartsWithIgnoreCase(locale, "el", &runtime);
149 JumpIfStartsWithIgnoreCase(locale, "lt", &runtime);
150 JumpIfStartsWithIgnoreCase(locale, "tr", &runtime);
151 Goto(&fast);
152
153 Bind(&fast);
154 }
155
156 // Early exit on empty string.
157 const TNode<Uint32T> length = LoadStringLengthAsWord32(string);
158 GotoIf(Word32Equal(length, Uint32Constant(0)), &return_string);
159
160 const TNode<Int32T> instance_type = to_direct.instance_type();
161 CSA_DCHECK(this,
162 Word32BinaryNot(IsIndirectStringInstanceType(instance_type)));
163
164 GotoIfNot(IsOneByteStringInstanceType(instance_type), &runtime);
165
166 // For short strings, do the conversion in CSA through the lookup table.
167
168 const TNode<String> dst = AllocateSeqOneByteString(length);
169
170 const int kMaxShortStringLength = 24; // Determined empirically.
171 GotoIf(Uint32GreaterThan(length, Uint32Constant(kMaxShortStringLength)),
172 &call_c);
173
174 {
175 const TNode<IntPtrT> dst_ptr = PointerToSeqStringData(dst);
176 TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_cursor, IntPtrConstant(0));
177
178 const TNode<IntPtrT> start_address =
179 ReinterpretCast<IntPtrT>(to_direct.PointerToData(&call_c));
180 const TNode<IntPtrT> end_address =
181 Signed(IntPtrAdd(start_address, ChangeUint32ToWord(length)));
182
183 const TNode<ExternalReference> to_lower_table_addr =
184 ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::intl_to_latin1_lower_table());
185
186 TVARIABLE(Word32T, var_did_change, Int32Constant(0));
187
188 VariableList push_vars({&var_cursor, &var_did_change}, zone());
189 BuildFastLoop<IntPtrT>(
190 push_vars, start_address, end_address,
191 [&](TNode<IntPtrT> current) {
192 TNode<Uint8T> c = Load<Uint8T>(current);
193 TNode<Uint8T> lower =
194 Load<Uint8T>(to_lower_table_addr, ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(c));
195 StoreNoWriteBarrier(MachineRepresentation::kWord8, dst_ptr,
196 var_cursor.value(), lower);
197
198 var_did_change =
199 Word32Or(Word32NotEqual(c, lower), var_did_change.value());
200
201 Increment(&var_cursor);
202 },
203 kCharSize, LoopUnrollingMode::kNo, IndexAdvanceMode::kPost);
204
205 // Return the original string if it remained unchanged in order to preserve
206 // e.g. internalization and private symbols (such as the preserved object
207 // hash) on the source string.
208 GotoIfNot(var_did_change.value(), &return_string);
209
210 ReturnFct(dst);
211 }
212
213 // Call into C for case conversion. The signature is:
214 // String ConvertOneByteToLower(String src, String dst);
215 BIND(&call_c);
216 {
217 const TNode<String> src = to_direct.string();
218
219 const TNode<ExternalReference> function_addr =
220 ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::intl_convert_one_byte_to_lower());
221
222 MachineType type_tagged = MachineType::AnyTagged();
223
224 const TNode<String> result = CAST(CallCFunction(
225 function_addr, type_tagged, std::make_pair(type_tagged, src),
226 std::make_pair(type_tagged, dst)));
227
228 ReturnFct(result);
229 }
230
231 BIND(&return_string);
232 ReturnFct(string);
233
234 BIND(&runtime);
235 if (kind == ToLowerCaseKind::kToLocaleLowerCase) {
236 ReturnFct(CallRuntime(Runtime::kStringToLocaleLowerCase, context, string,
237 maybe_locales));
238 } else {
239 DCHECK_EQ(kind, ToLowerCaseKind::kToLowerCase);
240 ReturnFct(CallRuntime(Runtime::kStringToLowerCaseIntl, NoContextConstant(),
241 string));
242 }
243}

245void IntlBuiltinsAssembler::ListFormatCommon(TNode<Context> context,
246 TNode<Int32T> argc,
247 Runtime::FunctionId format_func_id,
248 const char* method_name) {
249 CodeStubArguments args(this, argc);
250
251 // Label has_list(this);
252 // 1. Let lf be this value.
253 // 2. If Type(lf) is not Object, throw a TypeError exception.
254 TNode<Object> receiver = args.GetReceiver();
255
256 // 3. If lf does not have an [[InitializedListFormat]] internal slot, throw a
257 // TypeError exception.
258 ThrowIfNotInstanceType(context, receiver, JS_LIST_FORMAT_TYPE, method_name);
259 TNode<JSListFormat> list_format = CAST(receiver);
260
261 TNode<Object> list = args.GetOptionalArgumentValue(0);
262 {
263 // 4. Let stringList be ? StringListFromIterable(list).
264 TNode<Object> string_list =
265 CallBuiltin(Builtin::kStringListFromIterable, context, list);
266
267 // 6. Return ? FormatList(lf, stringList).
268 args.PopAndReturn(
269 CallRuntime(format_func_id, context, list_format, string_list));
270 }
271}

273TNode<JSArray> IntlBuiltinsAssembler::AllocateEmptyJSArray(
274 TNode<Context> context) {
275 return CodeStubAssembler::AllocateJSArray(
276 PACKED_ELEMENTS,
277 LoadJSArrayElementsMap(PACKED_ELEMENTS, LoadNativeContext(context)),
278 IntPtrConstant(0), SmiConstant(0));
279}
